+#### 1.15.8 Cortex Discovery and Selection
+
+The Brain maintains a **cortex registry** — an in-memory map of all installed and enabled cortices, grouped by role. On startup, the Brain loads all cortex manifests from:
+- `~/.config/tos/cortices/`
+- `/usr/share/tos/cortices/` (system-wide)
+- Any cortex installed via the Marketplace
+
+**Selection rules:**
+
+- At most one `assistant` cortex is active at a time. The user selects it in **Settings → AI → Assistant**.
+- Multiple `curator` cortices may be active simultaneously. The Brain routes `search`, `fetch`, and other curator calls to the most capable available cortex for the query type based on declared capabilities.
+- If no cortex satisfies a capability, the Brain logs a warning and returns an empty result rather than failing silently.
+- A cortex whose `[connection]` health check fails is marked `degraded` and skipped in routing until it recovers.
+
+**Settings → AI → Cortices:**
+```
+┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│  Cortices                                           │
+│                                                     │
+│  Assistant                                          │
+│  ● Ollama          ✓ online    [ Configure → ]     │
+│  ○ Anthropic       ✗ offline   [ Configure → ]     │
+│                                                     │
+│  Curators                                           │
+│  ✓ GitNexus        ✓ online    [ Configure → ]     │
+│  ✓ Filesystem      ✓ online    [ Configure → ]     │
+│  ✗ CocoIndex       ✗ offline   [ Configure → ]     │
+│                                                     │
+│  [ + Add Cortex ]                                   │
+└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
